52:56.000 --> 53:02.000
The respondent has the maximum freedom of response within the framework of the topics of the interested interviewer

53:02.000 --> 53:17.000
Deep interviews can be used to obtain information from experts, for example, industry experts or experts who work in your organization, as well as from individual respondents

53:17.000 --> 53:41.000
When we ask individual respondents one-on-one, when there is one interviewer and one respondent, for example, when some painful questions are asked about the state of health, about the treatment of certain diseases that cannot be said out loud or in a small group of respondents

53:41.000 --> 53:52.000
There are only three methods of deep interviews, methods of asking questions. These methods came to us from the concept of social psychology

53:53.000 --> 54:11.000
Remember, I said at the very beginning of our lectures that marketing research has absorbed all the experience and all the knowledge related to marketing, strategic marketing, statistics, mathematics and such humanities as sociology and psychology

54:11.000 --> 54:33.000
If sociology is a science about society, psychology is a science about the behavior of an individual, social psychology is a science about the behavior of an individual in society, that is, the behavior that changes depending on the influence of the external environment, depending on the state of society

54:33.000 --> 54:43.000
This science has developed some methods of sequential asking questions for various types of interviews

54:43.000 --> 54:57.000
If we talk about marketing, the basis of such questions is, of course, marketing problems, for example, the determination of the consumer's attitude to a particular type of product

54:57.000 --> 55:14.000
If we talk about other types of interviews, our presenters of some talk shows, for example, or TV interviewers, they also use the same kind of technique of asking questions

55:14.000 --> 55:29.000
We try to use the detailed deepening from the general to the private to study or invite, motivate, stimulate the respondents to demonstrate their own deep victories

55:30.000 --> 55:37.000
That is why these interviews are called deep, to identify deep preferences and relationships

55:38.000 --> 55:40.000
We continue with the methods of deep interviews

55:41.000 --> 56:00.000
The methods of deep interviews include methods of order of asking questions, for example, the method of the stairs, the sequence of asking questions from the general to the private, or the sequence of asking questions from the characteristics of the product, a gradual transition to the characteristics of the buyer, to the characteristics of the respondent

56:01.000 --> 56:12.000
Another method of asking questions, of conducting deep interviews is symbolic analysis, the analysis of the symbolic meaning of objects, comparison with opposites

56:12.000 --> 56:23.000
For example, the identification of associative thinking, the association of respondents with a particular object, a particular product, or an object, for example, a country

56:24.000 --> 56:35.000
For example, we talk about what we or respondents associate such countries as Germany, Japan, the United States of America, Russia, in particular

56:35.000 --> 56:52.000
There are some stereotypical associations or exclusive associations typical of a particular respondent, which allow us to make a list of these associations and find out the vocabulary of the respondents, who represent the target audience

56:52.000 --> 57:06.000
And the last method of conducting deep interviews is the explanation of hidden issues, the definition of certain weak points of a person, which correspond to his personal experiences

57:06.000 --> 57:24.000
For example, in my practice, there were respondents who wanted to hide or worry that they do not have a permanent job, and they were quite successful people, housewives, who led a family, took care of children

57:24.000 --> 57:35.000
And yet, they, as active consumers, were ashamed to admit that they are housewives and do not have a permanent job

57:35.000 --> 57:50.000
The sphere of application of deep interviews, detailed probe of the respondent, discussion of confidential, delicate, and not modest issues, in particular, some diseases or problems that respondents would like to hide from society

57:50.000 --> 58:07.000
Situations in which the opinion of others is suppressed by respondents, this often happens in deep interviews, for example, in focus groups, understanding of complex behavior, interviews with experts, interviews with competitors, and so on

58:07.000 --> 58:31.000
