58:31.000 --> 58:44.000
This scenario is usually called a topic guide in research companies. The key words in this definition are group, focused, and interview

58:44.000 --> 59:01.000
Despite the fact that the interview is organized and conducted by one moderator, a host or a researcher, and conducted with a group of respondents, nevertheless, the nature of this research is still an interview

59:01.000 --> 59:17.000
The interview is based on a detailed topic guide or scenario that is developed and discussed with the client in advance in order to identify certain problems and certain attitude of respondents to the research problem

59:17.000 --> 59:30.000
The goal of focus groups is to analyze the vocabulary, the conversation dictionary of consumers, to generate ideas for developing hypotheses, to study motives, needs, and perceptions of consumers

59:30.000 --> 59:42.000
For example, the perception of the new packaging of chocolate glazed Alexander's cheeses, which is produced by Rost Agroexport and offered at a premium price

59:42.000 --> 59:51.000
To study the emotional and behavioral reaction of consumers to the concept of new products, appearance, products, advertising, and so on

