01:16:24.920 --> 01:16:49.920
Because you don't see percentages, numbers, facts and data, but only some information that is passed on in a bulk during unstructured conversations, then such information, which is then analyzed, is called soft

01:16:49.920 --> 01:17:08.920
Because in contrast to quantitative information, which is called hard, how can it be analyzed? Of course, the easiest way is to make a protocol or a script of this research and then try to identify repetitions

01:17:08.920 --> 01:17:25.920
Based on these repetitions, if you see that the respondents repeat their opinion from group to group or during one group, then you can count them quantitatively

01:17:25.920 --> 01:17:37.920
If you don't see repetitions, then each opinion of the respondents, if it is significant for the project of research and information, must be analyzed and interpreted

